title: Oregon Ducks at Washington Huskies: Live updates & game chat
text:
The Oregon Ducks head north to take on the Washington Huskies on Saturday in a series the Huskies lead overall, but the Ducks have dominated in the last decade.
Here's what you need to know:
When: 7:30 p.m. Saturday
Where: Husky Stadium, Seattle
Latest line: Washington by 2
Weather at kickoff: 59 degrees, 49 percent chance of precipitation
On Air: TV on ESPN2, radio on radio on KXTG (750 AM, 102.9 FM), KUGN-AM (590), Sirius 136, XM 201
Oregon has won the last 11 games against Washington, the longest streak by either team against the other and the longest for the Ducks against any conference opponent.
Washington leads all-time in the series, 58-44-5 and is 33-25-4 in Seattle and as Oregon comes in with three losses already this season, the Huskies, may think this is the year they break through again.
Oregon is coming off its third loss of the season and comes in as 2-point underdogs.
Join us beginning during the game Saturday for live updates and analysis from Oregon State-Washington State.
